<div id="I_file">&lt;cstdio&gt;</div>
<h1>FILENAME_MAX</h1>
<div id="I_description">Maximum length of file names</div>
<section id="description">
This macro constant expands to an integral expression corresponding to the size needed for an array of <tt>char</tt> elements to hold the longest file name string allowed by the library. Or, if the library imposes no such restriction, it is set to the recommended size for character arrays intended to hold a file name.<br>
</section>
